<TITLE> BNP leader arrested in Chuadanga </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chuadanga, June 8 (bdnews24.com)  Detectives have arrested local BNP leader and Bhangabaria Union Parishad chairman Sanwar Hossain Laddu in Chuadanga town, a police official said Friday. Laddu, vice-president of Alamdanga upazila BNP, was arrested in a Thursday night raid, Alamdanga police chief Ruhul Amin told bdnews24.com. Amin said there were several cases against Laddu with Alamdanga Police Station on a number of charges, including aiding outlawed Maoist groups. Interrogators are questioning Laddu, Amin said, adding that the man has close clinks to extremist groups in the region. In 2005, the police arrested two leaders of the banned group Janajuddha at Laddu's home. bdnews24.c
